500|$|Hamdan v. <b>Rumsfeld,</b> , <b>is</b> a case {{in which}} the Supreme Court of the United States held that {{military}} commissions set up by the Bush administration to try detainees at Guantanamo Bay lack [...] "the power to proceed because its structures and procedures violate both the Uniform Code of Military Justice and the four Geneva Conventions signed in 1949." [...] Specifically, the ruling says that Common Article 3 of the Geneva Conventions was violated.|$|E
